title: ‘Star Wars’ Not Top Star at Comic-Con
text:
ben.fritz@wsj.com July 13, 2015 
SAN DIEGO—Fans won’t know who wins the movie’s titular battle until next year, but “Batman v Superman” emerged victorious among the movies and TV shows vying for buzz at Comic-Con International this past week. 
The superhero picture, which Time Warner Inc.’s Warner Bros. will release in March 2016, got 7.15 million engagements—anything from liking a video to sharing a friend’s post—across social-media platforms like Facebook, Twitter... To Read the Full Story, Subscribe or Sign In Popular on WSJ
